<topic id="3dc5a651-829e-4c61-9325-7738980ed456" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerConceptualDocument xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5">
    <summary>
      <para>This topic details the AMDL syntax and semantics of ATX-style section headers.</para>
    </summary>
    <introduction />
    <section address="Function">
      <title>Function</title>
      <content>
        <para>An ATX-style section header serves the following purposes:</para>
        <list class="ordered">
          <listItem>
            <para>Specify the section's title.</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>Terminate the topic's introduction, if one is present.</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>Start a new section.</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>Optionally, assign values to the section's attributes.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="Syntax">
      <title>Syntax</title>
      <content>
        <para>A line consisting of:</para>
        <list class="ordered">
          <listItem>
            <para>optionally, up to three space characters, followed by</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>two to six <codeInline>#</codeInline> characters, followed by</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>one or more space characters, followed by</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>text, followed by,</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>optionally, any number of space characters followed by any number of <codeInline>#</codeInline> characters, followed by,</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>optionally, an attribute enclosure.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
        <para>The text must be XML-escaped, i.e.</para>
        <list class="bullet">
          <listItem>
            <para>all occurrences of <codeInline>&lt;</codeInline> must be replaced with <codeInline>&amp;lt;</codeInline>,</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>all occurrences of <codeInline>&gt;</codeInline> must be replaced with <codeInline>&amp;gt;</codeInline>, and</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>all occurrences of <codeInline>&amp;</codeInline> must be replaced with <codeInline>&amp;amp;</codeInline>.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="Example">
      <title>Example</title>
      <content>
        <code language="none" title="AMDL">
## Example
</code>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="Example Output">
      <title>Example Output</title>
      <content>
        <para>The preceding section's header.</para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="Attributes">
      <title>Attributes</title>
      <content>
        <para>Sections can be assigned attributes through <legacyItalic>attribute enclosures</legacyItalic> using the following syntax:</para>
        <code language="none" title="AMDL">
	{#identifier .class1 .class2 name1=value1 name2=value2 ...}
</code>
        <para>All attribute values containing spaces, braces (<codeInline>{</codeInline> and <codeInline>}</codeInline>), or backslashes (<codeInline>\</codeInline>) <legacyItalic>must</legacyItalic> either</para>
        <list class="ordered">
          <listItem>
            <para>be enclosed in matching <codeInline>'</codeInline> or <codeInline>"</codeInline> characters, or</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>have all occurrences of these characters escaped, i.e. preceded by a <codeInline>\</codeInline> character.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
        <para>Section headers define the following attributes:</para>
      </content>
      <sections>
        <section address="identifier">
          <title>
            <codeInline>identifier</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a string value used for resolving internal links to the section.
If no value is specified, a unique identifier will be assigned based on the header text; detailed algorithm TBD.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="autoOutline">
          <title>
            <codeInline>autoOutline</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a boolean value indicating whether an automatic section outline should be generated.
If no attribute value is specified for a section with an ATX-style header, a section outline <legacyItalic>should not</legacyItalic> be generated.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="outlineDepth">
          <title>
            <codeInline>outlineDepth</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>an integer value indicating the maximum depth of the automatic section outline, if one is generated.
If no attribute value is specified, a zero-depth outline <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be generated.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="outlineLead">
          <title>
            <codeInline>outlineLead</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a string value that will be used as the lead-in text rendered before the automatic outline, if one is generated.
If an empty string is specified, the lead-in text <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be omitted.
If no attribute value is specified, a default lead-in text <legacyItalic>may</legacyItalic> be used.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="excludeSeeAlso">
          <title>
            <codeInline>excludeSeeAlso</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a boolean value indicating whether the <legacyItalic>See Also</legacyItalic> sub-section will be excluded from the automatic section outline, if both are generated.
If no attribute value is specified, the <legacyItalic>See Also</legacyItalic> sub-section <legacyItalic>should not</legacyItalic> be excluded, i.e. it <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be included.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
            <para>Class specifications <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be ignored, but <legacyItalic>must</legacyItalic> be accepted as valid input.</para>
          </content>
        </section>
      </sections>
    </section>
    <section address="Notes">
      <title>Notes</title>
      <content />
      <sections>
        <section address="Differences from PM">
          <title>Differences from PM</title>
          <content>
            <list class="ordered">
              <listItem>
                <para>Class specifications are undefined.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
      </sections>
    </section>
    <section address="amdl2maml Support">
      <title>amdl2maml Support</title>
      <content>
        <para>Partial, pending parser modification.</para>
        <list class="ordered">
          <listItem>
            <para>Outlines are suppressed for all ATX-style headers.</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>Attributes are unsupported.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
